## Getting Started

When you first open the app, you'll see the **intro splash screen** — the campaign name, character name, and level. Tap anywhere to dismiss it and enter the tracker.

> 💡 The intro splash also appears after a **Restart Session**, so it doubles as a "new session" signal.

---

## The Interface

The app is laid out like a handheld device with three columns:

```
┌──────────────┬────────────────────────┬──────────────┐
│              │  TITLEBAR              │              │
│  LEFT PANEL  │────────────────────────│  RIGHT PANEL │
│  (buttons)   │  PAGE CONTENT          │  (buttons)   │
│              │                        │              │
└──────────────┴────────────────────────┴──────────────┘
```

### Titlebar
- **Page name** — shown on the left
- **Status badge** — blinks in the centre when relevant:
  - `EDIT` (amber) — edit mode is active
  - `DYING` (red) — HP hit zero
  - `N COND` (red) — N conditions are currently active
- **Page counter** — shown on the right (e.g. `3 / 10`)

### Left Panel
Context-sensitive action buttons. Changes depending on mode:
- **Normal mode** — navigation buttons (page up/down, scroll up/down)
- **Edit mode** — field adjustment (INC/DEC) and field navigation (PREV/NEXT)
- **Dying mode** — death save buttons (YASS / NOOO)

### Right Panel
Context-sensitive action buttons:
- **Normal mode** — EDIT, HOME, and REST
- **Edit mode** — SAVE and CANCEL
- **Dying mode** — status info

