## Edit Mode

Most pages are **read-only** by default. To make changes, enter **Edit Mode**.

### Entering Edit Mode
Tap the **EDIT** button on the right panel. The titlebar will show a blinking amber `EDIT` badge.

> Pages 1 (INFO), 3 (SKILLS), and 5 (SPELLCASTING) are permanently read-only — the EDIT button is disabled on these pages.

### Making Changes
Once in edit mode:
1. Use **▲ PREV** / **▼ NEXT** on the left panel to select the field you want to change. The selected field is highlighted in amber.
2. Use **▲ INC** / **▼ DEC** to adjust the value.
3. Hold any button to repeat rapidly.

The **FIELD X/Y** indicator at the bottom of the left panel shows which field is selected.

### Saving or Cancelling
| Button | Action |
|--------|--------|
| `✓ SAVE` | Confirms all changes and exits edit mode |
| `✗ CANCEL` | Reverts everything back to how it was before you entered edit mode |

> ⚠️ Changes are applied live as you adjust — but CANCEL will fully revert them all, so don't worry about experimenting.

