## Pages Reference

### 1 — INFO
Read-only. Displays character name, class, subclass, race, background, and campaign. No interaction needed.

---

### 2 — ABILITIES
Displays all 8 ability scores and modifiers. Editable.

| Field | Notes |
|-------|-------|
| STR | Strength score |
| INT | Intelligence score |
| DEX | Dexterity score |
| WIS | Wisdom score |
| CON | Constitution score |
| CHA | Charisma score |
| PB | Proficiency Bonus — clamped between 2 and 6 |
| HI | Half-caster flag (toggles YES/NO) — used in skill calculations |

---

### 3 — SKILLS
Read-only. All skill and saving throw values are **auto-calculated** from your ability scores and proficiency bonus. Scroll through the list using `▲ UP` / `▼ DN`.

Proficiency indicators:
- `PRF` — proficient
- `EXP` — expertise (double proficiency)
- `·` — no proficiency (Jack of All Trades applies)

---

### 4 — COMBAT
Your core combat stats. Editable.

| Field | Notes |
|-------|-------|
| LEVEL | Character level |
| HP | Current hit points — capped at Max HP |
| MAX HP | Maximum hit points |
| AC | Armour Class |
| INIT | Initiative modifier |
| SPEED | Movement speed in feet |
| PASS PER | Passive Perception |

A **HP bar** at the top of the page shows your current health visually:
- White — healthy (above 50%)
- Amber — bloodied (25–50%)
- Red blinking — critical (below 25%)

---

### 5 — SPELLCASTING
Read-only. Auto-calculated from your CHA modifier and Proficiency Bonus.

| Stat | Formula |
|------|---------|
| Spell Save DC | 8 + PB + CHA mod |
| Casting Modifier | CHA mod |
| Spell Attack Bonus | PB + CHA mod |

---

### 6 — SPELL SLOTS
Tracks remaining spell slots per level. Only levels available at your current character level are shown.

- **INC** adds a slot back (recovering a used slot)
- **DEC** spends a slot

The pip display shows remaining slots visually. The fraction (e.g. `3/4`) shows remaining/max.

---

### 7 — FEATURES

> ⚠️ **Disclaimer:** This page is tailored specifically for **Malto Dextrin** and contains features unique to his character. If you are adapting this tracker for a different character, this page will need to be rebuilt to match their class features. See the README for developer guidance.

#### Bardic Inspiration
Tracks remaining Bardic Inspiration charges (max 4). Editable in edit mode (field 1).

#### Encouraging Song
Tracks remaining Encouraging Song uses. Maximum uses = Proficiency Bonus. Editable in edit mode (field 2).

#### Beast Mode
Malto is infected with lycanthropy. This toggle switches between **Human** and **Werewolf** forms.

**Tap the toggle directly on screen — no edit mode needed.**

| State | Effect |
|-------|--------|
| OFF (Human) | Normal stats |
| ON (Werewolf) | AC +1, Speed +10ft — applied automatically |

When Beast Mode is active, the app displays Malto's attack stats for reference:
- **Bite:** +4 to hit / 1d8+2 piercing
- **Claw:** +4 to hit / 2d4+2 slashing

#### Blood Lust Mode
When Beast Mode is ON and HP drops **below 50%**, the entire UI turns red — screen, panels, and all. The page title throbs. This is your visual warning that Malto is in a frenzied, dangerous state.

Toggling Beast Mode OFF reverts both the stat changes and the theming.

---

### 8 — CONDITIONS
Tracks all 15 standard D&D 5e conditions plus Exhaustion levels 1–6.

Conditions can only be toggled in **edit mode**:
1. Use **▲ PREV** / **▼ NEXT** to navigate to the condition
2. **INC** activates the condition, **DEC** deactivates it
3. For **Exhaustion**, INC/DEC steps through levels 1–6

Active conditions show in red. The titlebar shows a `N COND` badge whenever any condition is active.

---

### 9 — INVENTORY
Tracks carried items and quantities.

#### Adding Items
1. Type the item name in the text field at the bottom of the screen
2. Press **ADD** or hit **Enter**
3. Items are added with a quantity of 1

#### Editing Quantities
Enter edit mode, navigate to the item, and use INC/DEC to adjust the quantity. Setting quantity to 0 removes the item automatically.

#### Deleting Items
Tap the **✕** button on any item row — no edit mode needed.

---

### 10 — CURRENCY
Tracks Platinum, Gold, Silver, and Copper coins. Editable. Maximum 99,999 per denomination.

