## The REST Menu

Tap the amber **REST** button at the bottom of the right panel to open the REST overlay. It's accessible from any page at any time.

Tap **CLOSE** (same button) to dismiss it.

### Long Rest
Restores everything:
- HP → Max HP
- All spell slots restored
- Bardic Inspiration restored
- Encouraging Song restored
- Hit Dice recovered (half your total pool, minimum 1)

A confirmation screen shows you exactly what will be restored before you commit.

### Short Rest
Spend a hit die to recover HP:
1. Use INC/DEC to enter how many HP you're recovering (based on your dice roll)
2. Tap **✓ REST** to confirm — spends 1 hit die
3. Bardic Inspiration is only restored on a Short Rest at level 5+

The button is disabled if you have no hit dice remaining.

### Save / Load
Export your current save or import a previous one. See [Save & Load](#save--load) below.

### Restart Session
Resets the character for a fresh session while keeping your permanent data intact.

**What resets:**
- HP → Max HP
- All spell slots, Bardic Inspiration, Encouraging Song
- All hit dice restored
- All conditions cleared
- Beast Mode turned off (AC and Speed reverted)

**What is retained:**
- All ability scores and stats
- Inventory
- Currency
- Character level and Max HP

After restarting, the intro splash screen plays again.

