## Save & Load

The app saves automatically to your browser's local storage on every change. However, **local storage is per device, per browser** — your save on Chrome won't appear in Firefox, and your phone's save is separate from your laptop's.

To transfer saves between devices, use the **REST → SAVE / LOAD** screen.

### Exporting a Save
1. Open REST → SAVE / LOAD
2. Tap **⎘ COPY TO CLIPBOARD** under the EXPORT section
3. Paste the copied text into a note, text file, or cloud document (OneDrive, Google Drive, Mega, etc.)

### Importing a Save
1. Copy your previously exported save text from wherever you stored it
2. Open REST → SAVE / LOAD
3. Paste the text into the IMPORT box
4. Tap **↑ LOAD SAVE**

A green confirmation message appears on success. The overlay closes automatically after loading.

> ⚠️ If the text is corrupted or not a valid save, you'll see a red `✗ INVALID DATA` message. Nothing will be overwritten.

